  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This investment strengthens the monitoring systems of the lower basin of the Pilcomayo and to create public impact relative to the importance of the management of the basin. In this way, indigenous peoples and the small &#x201C;criollo&#x201D; ranchers may be constituted as social actors and be provided with a sufficiently efficient management tool to diminish the productive, economic, and human losses provoked by the river&#x2019;s variability (in many cases associated with governmental management errors in the basin), guaranteeing their territorial and food security, strengthening self-management processes toward the reconstruction of the alimentary sovereignty of the region and improving their capacity and quality of life.</narrative>
